Norilsk Nickel, Polyus Gold, United: Russia Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-06-21T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/norilsk-nickel-polyus-gold-united-russia-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 0.6 percent to 1,635.38. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index gained 0.8 percent to 1,872.45.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel’s
director selected Andrei Bugrov as chairman, tilting the board
away from billionaire Oleg Deripaska and toward rival
shareholder  Vladimir Potanin  in a fight to control Russia’s
biggest mining company. Norilsk Nickel rose 0.3 percent to 6,921
rubles.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX):  Mikhail Prokhorov , billionaire
chief executive officer and shareholder of OAO Polyus Gold, said
he won’t sell out of the company after its reverse takeover by
U.K.-registered unit KazakhGold Group Ltd. The Russian gold
producer declined 2.6 percent to 1,837.60 rubles.  United Aircraft Corp. (UNAC RX):  Russia ’s state-owned
development bank VEB signed an agreement on long-term
cooperation with United Aircraft Corp., which envisages
investments in building Tu-204SM, SSJ-100 and MS-21 airplanes,
as well as financing exports of the jets and infrastructure
projects, the bank said yesterday on its website. The aircraft
builder was little changed at 0.34 rubles.  SP Korolev Rocket & Space Corp. Energiya (RKKE RX):
Russia’s state-owned development bank VEB signed an agreement
with SP Korolev Rocket & Space Corp. Energiya, which foresees
investments in the creation of new space technologies and space
and rocket equipment, the Moscow-based bank said. The space
research company rose 0.5 percent to 8,225 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
